quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  30,16,"But as for those who shall not have believed, but treated our signs and the meeting of the next life as lies, they shall be given over to the torment"
  30,17,"Glorify God therefore when ye reach the evening, and when ye rise at morn"
  30,18,"And to Him be praise in the Heavens and on the Earth; and at twilight, and when ye rest at noon"
  30,19,"He bringeth forth the living out of the dead, and He bringeth forth the dead out of the living: and He quickeneth the earth when dead. Thus is it that ye too shall be brought forth"
  30,20,And one of his signs it is that He hath created you out of dust; then lo! ye become men who spread themselves far and wide
  30,21,"And one of his signs it is, that He hath created wives for you of your own species, that ye may dwell with them, and hath put love and tenderness between you. Herein truly are signs for those who reflect"
  30,22,"And among his signs are the creation of the Heavens and of the Earth, and your variety of tongues and colour. Herein truly are signs for all men"
  30,23,"And of his signs are your sleep by night and by day, and your goings in quest of his bounties. Herein truly are signs to those who hearken"
  30,24,"And of his signs are, that He sheweth you the lightning, a source of awe and hope; and that He sendeth down rain from the heaven and giveth life by it to the earth when dead. Herein truly are signs to those who understand"